{"title_page": "Bill Gertz", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n|name=Bill Gertz\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1952|3|28}}\n|birth_place=[[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|occupation=[[Newspaper editor|Editor]], [[columnist]], [[reporter]]\n}}\n\n'''William D.''' \"'''Bill'''\" '''Gertz''' (born March 28, 1952)<ref>[Bill Gertz' Twitter on March 28, 2014: \"Today's my birthday.\"]</ref> is an [[United States|American]] editor, [[columnist]] and reporter for ''[[The Washington Free Beacon]]'' and ''[[The Washington Times]]''. He is the author of six books and writes a weekly column on [[the Pentagon]] and [[national security]] issues called \"Inside the Ring\". During the administration of [[Bill Clinton]], Gertz was known for his stories exposing government secrets.<ref>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9904EED6173DF930A35751C1A9669C8B63&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=all Sieve City] ''[[The New York Times]]'' 12-03-2000</ref><ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/1995/0616/16204.html Psst! Have a White House Secret] ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]'' June 16, 1995</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nGertz was born on [[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. He is [[Jewish]]. He has attended [[Washington College]] and [[George Washington University]]. He has also written for ''[[National Review]]'', ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' and ''Air Force Magazine''. He has lectured on defense, national security, and media issues at the [[United States Department of Defense|Defense Department\u2019s]] National Security Leadership Program, [[Johns Hopkins University]] School of Advanced International Studies, the [[FBI National Academy]], the [[National Defense University]], and the [[CIA]].<ref>[http://www.regnery.com/authors/bio_billgertz.html Bill Gertz] [[Regnery Publishing]] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080905153746/http://www.regnery.com/authors/bio_billgertz.html |date=September 5, 2008 }}</ref> He has been a media fellow at the [[Hoover Institution on War, Revolution and Peace]] at [[Stanford University]].<ref>[http://www.worldtribune.com/worldtribune/gertz.asp Bill Gertz, U.S. National Security] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222030338/http://www.worldtribune.com/worldtribune/gertz.asp |date=2014-02-22 }} ''[[World Tribune]]''</ref> He lives in [[Maryland]].<ref>[http://www.randomhouse.com/author/results.pperl?authorid=58208 Bill Gertz author profile] [[Random House]]</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Gertz was subpoenaed to the [[Santa Ana, California]] federal court to testify in the case of [[Chi Mak]], who was convicted of providing [[United States Navy]] technology to [[China]]. Gertz refused to answer questions about his sources, citing the [[Fifth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Fifth Amendment]].<ref>[http://articles.latimes.com/2008/jul/25/local/me-mak25 Judge declines to order reporter to reveal sources] ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' July 25, 2008</ref>\n\n==Writings==\nDuring 1996 Gertz reported in the ''Washington Times'' on Chinese sales of nuclear technology to [[Pakistan]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1996/10/11/opinion/the-nuclear-gamble.html The Nuclear Gamble] ''The New York Times'', October 11. 1996</ref> In 1997 he reported on [[Russia]]n aid to [[Iran|Iran's]] [[nuclear weapon]] program, based on information given him by the Israeli intelligence agency [[Mossad]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/28/opinion/essay-iran-girds-for-war.html?pagewanted=all Iran Girds For War] ''The New York Times'', September 28, 1997</ref> In 1998 he reported on United States sale of [[missile]] technology to [[China]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1998/04/10/opinion/on-my-mind-the-missile-business.html?pagewanted=all The Missile Business] ''The New York Times'', April 10, 1998</ref> In 2004, Gertz wrote that Syria, possibly with the aid of Russian troops, [[WMD theories in the aftermath of the 2003 Iraq War|transferred]] Iraqi [[weapons of mass destruction]] stockpiles to its own military installations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/national/20041028-122637-6257r.htm |title=Russia tied to Iraq's missing arms |accessdate=2006-04-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060405233200/http://washingtontimes.com/national/20041028-122637-6257r.htm |archivedate=2006-04-05 }} ''[[The Washington Times]]'', October 28, 2004</ref>\n\nGertz's 2000 book, ''The China Threat: How the People's Republic Targets America'', presented the case that China's military was more modern and powerful than was its reputation in the United States military and intelligence communities.<ref>[http://www.geoffmetcalf.com/qa/19668.html Is the 'China threat' real?] [[Geoff Metcalf]]</ref> His 2002 book, ''Breakdown: How America's Intelligence Failures Led to Sept. 11'', examined the activities of United States intelligence agencies prior to the 2001 terrorist attacks.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/20/books/books-of-the-times-a-catastrophic-failure-to-think-the-unthinkable.html?pagewanted=print A Catastrophic Failure To Think the Unthinkable] ''The New York Times'' November 20, 2002</ref> His 2004 book, ''Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'', accused United States allies, including [[France]] and [[Germany]] of helping to arm [[Terrorism|terrorists]].<ref>[http://www.cfif.org/htdocs/freedomline/current/in_our_opinion/bill-gertz-treachery-interview.htm Author Bill Gertz Discusses \u2018Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'] [[Center for Individual Freedom]]</ref> His 2008 book, ''The Failure Factory: How Unelected Bureaucrats, Liberal Democrats, and Big Government Republicans Are Undermining America's Security and Leading Us to War'', said that many federal bureaucrats hold liberal views on foreign policy.<ref>[http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,436842,00.html Where's the Real Power in Washington? New Book Claims It's Not in the Oval Office] [[Fox News]], October 13, 2008</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* ''[[Betrayal: How the Clinton Administration Undermined American Security]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[The China Threat: How the People's Republic Targets America]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Breakdown: How America's Intelligence Failures Led to September 11]]'' (2002)\n* ''Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'' (2004)\n* ''[[Enemies: How America's Foes Steal Our Vital Secrets \u2013 And How We Let It Happen]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[The Failure Factory|The Failure Factory: How Unelected Bureaucrats, Liberal Democrats, and Big Government Republicans Are Undermining America's Security and Leading Us to War]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[iWar: War and Peace in the Information Age]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Deceiving the Sky: Inside Communist China's Drive for Global Supremacy]]'' (2019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.gertzfile.com/ Official website]\n* {{C-SPAN|billgertz}}\n**[http://www.c-spanvideo.org/program/283054-1 ''In Depth'' interview with Gertz, January 4, 2009]\n**[https://www.c-span.org/video/?464479-1/after-words-bill-gertz After Words with Bill Gertz September 30, 2019]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gertz, Bill}}\n[[Category:American male journalists]]\n[[Category:George Washington University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Long Island]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:The Washington Times people]]\n[[Category:Washington College alumni]]\n[[Category:American anti-communists]]\n[[Category:National Review people]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n|name=Bill Gertz\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1952|3|28}}\n|birth_place=[[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|occupation=[[Newspaper editor|Editor]], [[columnist]], [[reporter]]\n}}\n\n'''William D.''' \"'''Bill'''\" '''Gertz''' (born March 28, 1952)<ref>[Bill Gertz' Twitter on March 28, 2014: \"Today's my birthday.\"]</ref> is an [[United States|American]] editor, [[columnist]] and reporter for ''[[The Washington Free Beacon]]'' and ''[[The Washington Times]]''. He is the author of six books and writes a weekly column on [[the Pentagon]] and [[national security]] issues called \"Inside the Ring\". During the administration of [[Bill Clinton]], Gertz was known for his stories exposing government secrets.<ref>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9904EED6173DF930A35751C1A9669C8B63&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=all Sieve City] ''[[The New York Times]]'' 12-03-2000</ref><ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/1995/0616/16204.html Psst! Have a White House Secret] ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]'' June 16, 1995</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nGertz was born on [[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. He is [[Jewish]]. He has attended [[Washington College]] and [[George Washington University]]. He has also written for ''[[National Review]]'', ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' and ''Air Force Magazine''. He has lectured on defense, national security, and media issues at the [[United States Department of Defense|Defense Department\u2019s]] National Security Leadership Program, [[Johns Hopkins University]] School of Advanced International Studies, the [[FBI National Academy]], the [[National Defense University]], and the [[CIA]].<ref>[http://www.regnery.com/authors/bio_billgertz.html Bill Gertz] [[Regnery Publishing]] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080905153746/http://www.regnery.com/authors/bio_billgertz.html |date=September 5, 2008 }}</ref> He has been a media fellow at the [[Hoover Institution on War, Revolution and Peace]] at [[Stanford University]].<ref>[http://www.worldtribune.com/worldtribune/gertz.asp Bill Gertz, U.S. National Security] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222030338/http://www.worldtribune.com/worldtribune/gertz.asp |date=2014-02-22 }} ''[[World Tribune]]''</ref> He lives in [[Maryland]].<ref>[http://www.randomhouse.com/author/results.pperl?authorid=58208 Bill Gertz author profile] [[Random House]]</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Gertz was subpoenaed to the [[Santa Ana, California]] federal court to testify in the case of [[Chi Mak]], who was convicted of providing [[United States Navy]] technology to [[China]]. Gertz refused to answer questions about his sources, citing the [[Fifth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Fifth Amendment]].<ref>[http://articles.latimes.com/2008/jul/25/local/me-mak25 Judge declines to order reporter to reveal sources] ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' July 25, 2008</ref>\n\n==Writings==\nDuring 1996 Gertz reported in the ''Washington Times'' on Chinese sales of nuclear technology to [[Pakistan]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1996/10/11/opinion/the-nuclear-gamble.html The Nuclear Gamble] ''The New York Times'', October 11. 1996</ref> In 1997 he reported on [[Russia]]n aid to [[Iran|Iran's]] [[nuclear weapon]] program, based on information given him by the Israeli intelligence agency [[Mossad]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/28/opinion/essay-iran-girds-for-war.html?pagewanted=all Iran Girds For War] ''The New York Times'', September 28, 1997</ref> In 1998 he reported on United States sale of [[missile]] technology to [[China]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1998/04/10/opinion/on-my-mind-the-missile-business.html?pagewanted=all The Missile Business] ''The New York Times'', April 10, 1998</ref> In 2004, Gertz wrote that Syria, possibly with the aid of Russian troops, [[WMD theories in the aftermath of the 2003 Iraq War|transferred]] Iraqi [[weapons of mass destruction]] stockpiles to its own military installations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/national/20041028-122637-6257r.htm |title=Russia tied to Iraq's missing arms |accessdate=2006-04-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060405233200/http://washingtontimes.com/national/20041028-122637-6257r.htm |archivedate=2006-04-05 }} ''[[The Washington Times]]'', October 28, 2004</ref>\n\nGertz's 2000 book, ''The China Threat: How the People's Republic Targets America'', presented the case that China's military was more modern and powerful than was its reputation in the United States military and intelligence communities.<ref>[http://www.geoffmetcalf.com/qa/19668.html Is the 'China threat' real?] [[Geoff Metcalf]]</ref> His 2002 book, ''Breakdown: How America's Intelligence Failures Led to Sept. 11'', examined the activities of United States intelligence agencies prior to the 2001 terrorist attacks.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/20/books/books-of-the-times-a-catastrophic-failure-to-think-the-unthinkable.html?pagewanted=print A Catastrophic Failure To Think the Unthinkable] ''The New York Times'' November 20, 2002</ref> His 2004 book, ''Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'', accused United States allies, including [[France]] and [[Germany]] of helping to arm [[Terrorism|terrorists]].<ref>[http://www.cfif.org/htdocs/freedomline/current/in_our_opinion/bill-gertz-treachery-interview.htm Author Bill Gertz Discusses \u2018Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'] [[Center for Individual Freedom]]</ref> His 2008 book, ''The Failure Factory: How Unelected Bureaucrats, Liberal Democrats, and Big Government Republicans Are Undermining America's Security and Leading Us to War'', said that many federal bureaucrats hold liberal views on foreign policy.<ref>[http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,436842,00.html Where's the Real Power in Washington? New Book Claims It's Not in the Oval Office] [[Fox News]], October 13, 2008</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* ''[[Betrayal: How the Clinton Administration Undermined American Security]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[The China Threat: How the People's Republic Targets America]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Breakdown: How America's Intelligence Failures Led to September 11]]'' (2002)\n* ''Treachery: How America\u2019s Friends and Foes Are Secretly Arming Our Enemies'' (2004)\n* ''[[Enemies: How America's Foes Steal Our Vital Secrets \u2013 And How We Let It Happen]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[The Failure Factory|The Failure Factory: How Unelected Bureaucrats, Liberal Democrats, and Big Government Republicans Are Undermining America's Security and Leading Us to War]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[iWar: War and Peace in the Information Age]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Deceiving the Sky: Inside Communist China's Drive for Global Supremacy]]'' (2019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.gertzfile.com/ Official website]\n* {{C-SPAN|billgertz}}\n**[http://www.c-spanvideo.org/program/283054-1 ''In Depth'' interview with Gertz, January 4, 2009]\n**[https://www.c-span.org/video/?464479-1/after-words-bill-gertz After Words with Bill Gertz September 30, 2019]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gertz, Bill}}\n[[Category:American male journalists]]\n[[Category:George Washington University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Long Island]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:The Washington Times people]]\n[[Category:Washington College alumni]]\n[[Category:American anti-communists]]\n[[Category:National Review people]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Gertz"}
